{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"47e36525-72e2-4615-b81d-95ef28506a29","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types from files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01TpjUKHQr7ZJY9GyaeQDaRC","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f72ad7482f184b3cab43c2e97e755687/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f72ad7482f184b3cab43c2e97e755687/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"a6544b60-756f-4ebc-b45d-ec1f0134dd8c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\n`Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, so `Domain.fs` must come first. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":383,"requestId":"7824:12F3AB:F36C2:12F115:69F549EF"},"id":"2d23d8a2-8402-4b9e-86f4-9aa2af86d3d9","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:48:55.067Z","parentId":"e768bfd3-e3d1-4cb7-b9b7-ff61e3cc2fad"}
